Use CSS transform and transition for a card flip effect. Use two sides in a container.

**HTML:**
```html
<div class="flip-card">
  <div class="flip-inner">
    <div class="flip-front">Front</div>
    <div class="flip-back">Back</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

**CSS:**
```css
.flip-card {
  width: 200px;
  height: 300px;
  perspective: 1000px;
}
.flip-inner {
  position: relative;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  transition: transform 0.6s;
  transform-style: preserve-3d;
}
.flip-card:hover .flip-inner {
  transform: rotateY(180deg);
}
.flip-front, .flip-back {
  position: absolute;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  backface-visibility: hidden;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
}
.flip-front {
  background: #ddd;
}
.flip-back {
  background: #555;
  color: white;
  transform: rotateY(180deg);
}
```

