Use HTML checkbox and CSS to style a toggle button. Use :checked for state.

**HTML:**
```html
<label class="toggle">
  <input type="checkbox">
  <span class="slider"></span>
</label>
```

**CSS:**
```css
.toggle {
  position: relative;
  display: inline-block;
  width: 60px;
  height: 34px;
}
.toggle input {
  opacity: 0;
  width: 0;
  height: 0;
}
.slider {
  position: absolute;
  cursor: pointer;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  right: 0;
  bottom: 0;
  background: #ccc;
  transition: 0.4s;
  border-radius: 34px;
}
.slider:before {
  position: absolute;
  content: "";
  height: 26px;
  width: 26px;
  left: 4px;
  bottom: 4px;
  background: white;
  transition: 0.4s;
  border-radius: 50%;
}
input:checked + .slider {
  background: green;
}
input:checked + .slider:before {
  transform: translateX(26px);
}
```

